\p{Let #{V} be a finite-dimensional [[vectsp-0020]]s over #{\FF}. Suppose we have #{B=(e_{1},\dots,e_{n})} and #{C=(f_{1},\dots,f_{n})} are [orthonormal bases](vectsp-002D) for #{V}. We define the \define{Change of basis} linear transformation is the matrix #{S\in\FF^{n\times n}} defined by
##{s_{i,j}=\langle e_{j},f_{i}\rangle}}